===Etymology 2===
Old English ''[[clifian]]'', from West Germanic ''*[[klibajanan]]'', from Proto-Indo-European root ''*[[gloi-]]'' (to stick).

====Verb====
{{en-verb|cleav|ing}}
#''(intransitive)'' To [[cling]], [[adhere]] or [[stick]] [[fast]] to something
#''(intransitive)'' To be faithful: cleave to one’s principles.

